Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.09,0:01:17.58,辉中,,0,0,0,,So TLOU2 opens with Joel, discussing the ending events of the first game.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.58,0:01:20.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,The cameras focused on the threat board of the guitar,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.34,0:01:23.91,辉中,,0,0,0,,which has a very distinctive symbol on it, which will be important later.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.91,0:01:27.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,I want you to take a mental picture of this scene
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.25,0:01:30.60,辉中,,0,0,0,,because it's going to come back all the way at the end of the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.60,0:01:33.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,During this conversation between Joel and Tommy,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.81,0:01:38.37,辉中,,0,0,0,,Joel explains his decision to save Ellie over humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.37,0:01:43.86,辉中,,0,0,0,,Now even this point was one of controversy when the game first launched.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.86,0:01:45.42,辉中,,0,0,0,,You see, at the end of the first game,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.42,0:01:50.91,辉中,,0,0,0,,there was a serious question as to whether or not the Fireflies would be able to develop a vaccine at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.91,0:01:55.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,It was one of the reasons that a lot of people thought that Joel's actions were highly justified.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.32,0:01:58.89,辉中,,0,0,0,,Not just in that he was saving Ellie, his "daughter character",
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.89,0:02:02.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,but rather that he didn't want to sacrifice Ellie's life
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.78,0:02:07.14,辉中,,0,0,0,,for the sake of a cause which likely wouldn't find success any ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.14,0:02:11.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,After all, the fireflies in the first game are pretty damn in competent.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.52,0:02:14.67,辉中,,0,0,0,,They hire somebody from outside their ranks to transport,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.67,0:02:19.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,who is likely the most important human being who has ever lived in the form of Ellie
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.29,0:02:24.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,all the way across the country in order to hopefully develop a vaccine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.21,0:02:28.38,辉中,,0,0,0,,But when you get there and you explore the hospital at the end of the first game,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.38,0:02:34.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,you find out that a lot of the doctors involved in this procedure are unsure as to whether or not it's even possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.68,0:02:39.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,After all, literally, every single person in this hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.35,0:02:46.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,is completely inexperienced in developing a vaccine for a fungus such as this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.29,0:02:49.73,辉中,,0,0,0,,But the fireflies argument is that at least there's a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.73,0:02:54.01,辉中,,0,0,0,,If Ellie runs off, and they don't even attempt to extract any of the antibodies
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.01,0:02:59.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,or whatever the hell his inside of her brain that allows her to survive after having a bite.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.25,0:03:02.88,辉中,,0,0,0,,Then they will never know whether or not a vaccine is possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.88,0:03:07.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,But if they crack her skull open and try and develop some sort of vaccine at the very least,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.62,0:03:09.15,辉中,,0,0,0,,then there's a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.15,0:03:11.97,辉中,,0,0,0,,However, in the opening for this sequel,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.97,0:03:14.39,辉中,,0,0,0,,We see that Joel is pretty confident
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.39,0:03:18.60,辉中,,0,0,0,,that they were trying to develop a vaccine and that they likely would have been able to,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.60,0:03:19.95,辉中,,0,0,0,,but that it would have killed her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.95,0:03:24.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,But it's Tommy's expression that I think sets the tone
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.44,0:03:27.87,辉中,,0,0,0,,for how the player is supposed to feel about joel's decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.87,0:03:33.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,He's stunned, but at the same time he can't really blame Joel for the choice that he made.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.45,0:03:36.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,After all, later on, in this very intro sequence,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.96,0:03:40.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,Tommy turns to Joel and tells him that he would have done the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.56,0:03:46.14,辉中,,0,0,0,,Regardless, the choice to open the game in this way is very, very important.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.14,0:03:50.55,辉中,,0,0,0,,The writers over at Naughty Dog wanted to remind the player of what Joel had done
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.55,0:03:56.93,辉中,,0,0,0,,and establish that as the fulcrum from which every narrative mechanism will hinge.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.04,0:04:01.26,辉中,,0,0,0,,After this conversation, Tommy still unsure of how to react,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.26,0:04:05.31,辉中,,0,0,0,,simply tells Joel to hop on his horse and head back into town.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.31,0:04:08.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,It buys Tommy some time in order to form an opinion,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.40,0:04:12.93,辉中,,0,0,0,,and it also gives the player a chance to settle back into this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.93,0:04:15.54,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's really common for sequels to rush into things,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.54,0:04:19.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,Giving the player a chance to see something new and fresh and different
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.05,0:04:21.87,辉中,,0,0,0,,that they only could have dreamed of in the first game.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.87,0:04:25.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,However, and thankfully Naughty Dog doesn't do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.35,0:04:28.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,They take their time during this intro to set things up,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.29,0:04:30.66,辉中,,0,0,0,,and I think it works very, very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.66,0:04:33.87,辉中,,0,0,0,,You ride through a beautiful landscape and come up on Jackson,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.87,0:04:38.37,辉中,,0,0,0,,and it's at this time that we get our first look at a fully realized Jackson,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.37,0:04:42.85,辉中,,0,0,0,,the city that we saw peak of at the end of the first game, but that we could only imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.85,0:04:44.67,辉中,,0,0,0,,And I've got to hand it to Naughty Dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.67,0:04:51.57,辉中,,0,0,0,,This opening sequence has one of the most well realized cities I've ever seen in any video game ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.57,0:04:53.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,It truly is fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.52,0:05:01.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,Every NPC, every animation, every building, every step in the snow is detailed and realistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.62,0:05:03.48,辉中,,0,0,0,,As far as immersion is concerned,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.48,0:05:08.60,辉中,,0,0,0,,I think this is one of the most fantastically effective games that's ever been created.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.60,0:05:10.53,辉中,,0,0,0,,After you reach the inside of the city,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.53,0:05:16.26,辉中,,0,0,0,,Tommy and Joel hop off of their horses and Tommy offers to stow Joel's horse for him,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.26,0:05:19.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,while also saying that he'll take the truth to his grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.35,0:05:21.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,This implies a couple of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.06,0:05:24.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,For one, it might seem as though he's referring directly to Ellie
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.20,0:05:28.74,辉中,,0,0,0,,that if Ellie were to find out this truth, it would cause a lot of problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.74,0:05:31.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,After all, as far as Ellie is concerned,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.08,0:05:35.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,Joel simply took Ellie after a bunch of tests were run,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.40,0:05:40.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,and it was clear that she was not going to be able to provide any sort of help towards a vaccine at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.77,0:05:42.03,辉中,,0,0,0,,At the end of the first game,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.03,0:05:45.54,辉中,,0,0,0,,it's pretty clear that Ellie sees through this lie, that Joel is telling,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.54,0:05:48.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,or at the very least, she expects that there's more to this story.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.84,0:05:52.14,辉中,,0,0,0,,For the sake of their relationship, she simply goes along with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.14,0:05:54.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,However, I think there's another implication to this as well,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.78,0:05:59.19,辉中,,0,0,0,,and that is that if other people in the camp were to find out what Joel had done,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.19,0:06:01.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,I am not so sure that they would approve of it either.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.62,0:06:06.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,Again, we can talk all day about how incompetent the fireflies were in the first game.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.21,0:06:08.31,辉中,,0,0,0,,And I think there's a real argument to be had there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.31,0:06:11.46,辉中,,0,0,0,,I mean, if I had to entrust them with the fate of humanity,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.46,0:06:14.28,辉中,,0,0,0,,I would hop on the next asteroid off the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.28,0:06:18.24,辉中,,0,0,0,,What I mean, though, is that Naughty Dog is trying to tell his story,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.24,0:06:22.47,辉中,,0,0,0,,and they're framing the plot points the way that they want you the player to see them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.47,0:06:24.15,辉中,,0,0,0,,For the sake of this story,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.15,0:06:28.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,it's important to understand that the fireflies were the ones that were trying to save humanity
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.84,0:06:36.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,and were apparently on the cusp of developing a vaccine to save countless millions of lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.06,0:06:40.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,And once again, for the sake of this story, that's been told in TLOU2,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.84,0:06:43.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,Joel is the one that undid that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.52,0:06:49.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,Again, at the very least, if Ellie had gone under the knife, there would have been a chance for a vaccine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.68,0:06:55.71,辉中,,0,0,0,,By killing the doctors that were about to operate on Ellie and potentially develop a vaccine,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.71,0:06:58.23,辉中,,0,0,0,,he effectively saved his "daughter figure",
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.23,0:07:02.67,辉中,,0,0,0,,but he damned all of humanity for the rest of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.67,0:07:06.39,辉中,,0,0,0,,In other words, he strained at a gnat but swallowed a camel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.39,0:07:11.31,辉中,,0,0,0,,He traded what seemed to be a smaller evil for a much much larger evil,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.31,0:07:17.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,and he did this because his judgment was clouded by his own personal wants and wishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.10,0:07:23.13,辉中,,0,0,0,,This isn't to say that Joel would or does regret any of this in this particular sequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.13,0:07:26.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,But it is to say that the players should start seriously considering
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.44,0:07:32.31,辉中,,0,0,0,,whether or not Joel's actions were justified, or perhaps even whether or not they were right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.31,0:07:35.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,But don't worry, Naughty Dog is going to help you think about this
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.12,0:07:41.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,by constantly bringing it up using flashbacks. as Elie grew up in Jackson.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.25,0:07:43.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,and I promise you before you know it,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.05,0:07:46.74,辉中,,0,0,0,,you might even be convinced that Joel is in fact a villain.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.74,0:07:52.65,辉中,,0,0,0,,This isn't to say that Joel is unlikable character that you should hate him or wish that he were dead,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.65,0:07:56.76,辉中,,0,0,0,,but rather Joel is the one that damned humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.76,0:08:03.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,If you tell any other story and there's a character which damns humanity for the sake of one single person,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.90,0:08:06.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,we would say he's a bad guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.00,0:08:08.64,辉中,,0,0,0,,Or perhaps we wouldn't even say bad guy,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.64,0:08:13.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,we would simply say that he was a confused or perhaps mistaken individual,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.56,0:08:15.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,whose motivations were complex.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.90,0:08:20.94,辉中,,0,0,0,,But the point is, it's not as simple as hero and villain.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.94,0:08:23.19,辉中,,0,0,0,,There is a lot of gray in between.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.19,0:08:28.83,辉中,,0,0,0,,Now this intro sequence is just shortly after Joel's arrival, while Ellie is still young.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.83,0:08:34.53,辉中,,0,0,0,,She's living out of grandmothers suite in the back of the house that is presumably owned by Joel.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.53,0:08:36.60,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's super cute that she has her own space,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.60,0:08:41.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,but it even now shows and tells a lot about their relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.90,0:08:46.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,Now granted, Joel is a middle aged man that found this little girl,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.62,0:08:49.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,and he took her halfway across the country,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.32,0:08:51.57,辉中,,0,0,0,,rescued her from a bunch of cannibals,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.57,0:08:56.67,辉中,,0,0,0,,and now has her in a town that his brother runs with his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.67,0:09:01.71,辉中,,0,0,0,,it could be presumed that her staying in his house could be considered an appropriate.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.71,0:09:03.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,But I don't think that's the point here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.78,0:09:08.58,辉中,,0,0,0,,Joel is Ellie's "father figure", and I don't think that's a controversial thing to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.58,0:09:15.75,辉中,,0,0,0,,The fact that Ellie wants space, physical space separated from him means a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.75,0:09:18.59,辉中,,0,0,0,,Regardless, we see Ellie and she's drawing something
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.59,0:09:21.27,辉中,,0,0,0,,that will come back time and time again throughout the rest of the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.27,0:09:25.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,She's actually pretty artsy and gifted, artistically,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.05,0:09:29.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,you'll see this in the note book that you'll be using throughout the course of the main game.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.34,0:09:33.67,辉中,,0,0,0,,She often draws pictures of what she sees or sketches out different things
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.67,0:09:36.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,in order to remind her to return to that area
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.52,0:09:41.30,辉中,,0,0,0,,or simply to keep a journal of the events and happenings of the main story.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.40,0:09:44.01,辉中,,0,0,0,,She's listening to music when Joel comes in.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.01,0:09:48.99,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's a really cute and awkward moment, but it's pretty damn sweet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.99,0:09:52.83,辉中,,0,0,0,,It doesn't take a body language expert to see that there's a lot of tension here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.83,0:09:57.15,辉中,,0,0,0,,Jole's unsure of how to stand, where to move, how to talk, how to relate to her,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.15,0:09:59.64,辉中,,0,0,0,,and Ellie picks up on this as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.64,0:10:01.71,辉中,,0,0,0,,The tension is really palpable.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.71,0:10:05.94,辉中,,0,0,0,,They both know what happened in Utah hasn't been resolved,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.94,0:10:08.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,but neither knows how to broach the topic,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.16,0:10:10.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,so they simply delay it and push it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.56,0:10:16.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,But the point of this sequence is where Joel to express how much he needs Ellie in his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.68,0:10:21.51,辉中,,0,0,0,,Let's all just take a moment to relax and appreciate how beautiful the scenery is,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.51,0:10:24.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,and how Ellie responds in classic Ellie fashion.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.00,0:10:37.92,辉中,,0,0,0,,如果有一天我失去了你
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.09,0:10:41.60,辉中,,0,0,0,,我肯定会失去自我
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.67,0:10:46.47,辉中,,0,0,0,,我在这里找到的一切
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.64,0:10:49.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,都不是只靠我自己
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.69,0:10:54.79,辉中,,0,0,0,,尝试吧，或许你能做到
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.79,0:10:58.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,成就现在的我
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.62,0:11:03.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,我丢失的一切
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.75,0:11:07.69,辉中,,0,0,0,,早已不再需要
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.58,0:11:11.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为我相信
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.96,0:11:18.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,我深信因我可预见
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.00,0:11:22.58,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们未来的日子
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.60,0:11:26.61,辉中,,0,0,0,,有你与我作伴
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.48,0:11:42.88,辉中,,0,0,0,,还不错吧
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.63,0:11:45.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,嗯……
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.92,0:11:48.23,辉中,,0,0,0,,不难听
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.00,0:11:52.57,辉中,,0,0,0,,我就当作是夸奖了
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.46,0:11:55.02,辉中,,0,0,0,,And I'm sure I don't need to tell you this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.02,0:11:59.31,辉中,,0,0,0,,but this song is going to come up time and time again throughout the course of the main story.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.31,0:12:01.53,辉中,,0,0,0,,So make sure that you remember it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.53,0:12:05.91,辉中,,0,0,0,,Though I'm sure I don't need to tell you that because you'll likely remember this for the rest of your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.91,0:12:08.66,辉中,,0,0,0,,considering how unbelievably touching it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.66,0:12:11.94,辉中,,0,0,0,,Also a funny little thing that Neil Druckman tweeted out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.94,0:12:16.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,Apparently he had been asked many many times on Twitter and in person
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.38,0:12:19.11,辉中,,0,0,0,,why Pearl Jam's "Future Days" was used in the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.11,0:12:25.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,People ask this because the song didn't actually drop until October of 2013 officially.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.05,0:12:28.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,And that is actually a month after outbreak day in this universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.80,0:12:32.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,so it shouldn't have actually existed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.06,0:12:33.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,Neil Druckman responded by saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.81,0:12:40.83,辉注 twitter,,300,0,200,,感谢您的提问！其实……这首歌在专辑发布的几个月\N之前就在YouTube上有一场live了。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.83,0:12:43.14,辉中,,0,0,0,,And you can actually go look it up on Youtube,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.14,0:12:45.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,and sure enough, Pearl jam performed this live,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.81,0:12:51.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,and that video was posted on July, 26th of 2013.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.06,0:12:53.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,That's the actual date of the video.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.25,0:12:58.59,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's a perfect example of Naughty Dog's excessive attention to detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.59,0:13:05.73,辉中,,0,0,0,,I don't think anybody would have cared, particularly if this song released three years after outbreak day,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.73,0:13:11.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,but the fact that they took it upon themselves to find a song that fit the theme and the tone of the game
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.44,0:13:15.39,辉中,,0,0,0,,and that fits so perfectly within Joel and Ellie's relationship,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.39,0:13:19.71,辉中,,0,0,0,,and then to also make sure that it fit in with the timeline they were dealing with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.71,0:13:21.15,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.15,0:13:25.23,辉中,,0,0,0,,But once again its one of the examples of Naughty Dog's perfectionism.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.23,0:13:28.53,辉中,,0,0,0,,They don't need to care about these little things, but they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.53,0:13:32.19,辉中,,0,0,0,,And that's what sets them apart, whether you love them or hate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.19,0:13:36.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,After this touching flashback, we cut to Ellie, waking up late.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.00,0:13:39.53,辉中,,0,0,0,,Jesse, a character we'll get to see a little bit throughout the course of the game
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.53,0:13:42.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,is at her front door, giving her crap for sleeping in.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.44,0:13:46.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,Over the next ten or so minutes as you walk through the town,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.08,0:13:51.60,辉中,,0,0,0,,you have a recap of everything that went down and then some in the trailer from E3 2018.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.60,0:13:53.49,辉中,,0,0,0,,Now I found this particularly interesting,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.49,0:13:57.87,辉中,,0,0,0,,because that sequence where Dina and Ellie share their first kiss,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.87,0:14:00.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,I thought was a pretty important sequence to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.78,0:14:04.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,But Naughty Dog doesn't show it to the player, at least not right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.41,0:14:08.28,辉中,,0,0,0,,Instead, they rely on the dialog to explain what happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.28,0:14:10.89,辉中,,0,0,0,,but I can't help to notice that this is the first instance
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.89,0:14:15.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,where trailers are important to a contextual grasp of the game itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.45,0:14:17.28,辉中,,0,0,0,,because, after all, in this case,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.28,0:14:21.71,辉中,,0,0,0,,the scene that's being discussed isn't actually shown to the player
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.71,0:14:24.79,辉中,,0,0,0,,until the last 15 or so minutes of the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.79,0:14:32.09,辉中,,0,0,0,,Time and time again, stuff that was shown in the trailers is either changed drastically or is moved around
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.09,0:14:37.99,辉中,,0,0,0,,such that you need to have seen the trailer in order to truly understand what's going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.99,0:14:42.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,Now I understand that it's a small thing to point out or be frustrated by,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.07,0:14:46.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,because after all chances are every single person who bought the game had seen that trailer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.80,0:14:51.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,However, I still think it's strange to show a scene in a trailer,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.06,0:14:54.87,辉中,,0,0,0,,but then not show it in the game when that item is being discussed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.87,0:14:57.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's one of countless times in this game,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.12,0:15:01.22,辉中,,0,0,0,,when Naughty Dog will take a sequence, cut it up into fifteen different parts
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.22,0:15:05.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,and then spread it randomly, seemingly throughout the course of the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.04,0:15:07.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,Sometimes I think it helps with pacing
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.04,0:15:11.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,by giving the player a break from a very stressful environment or activity,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.52,0:15:15.75,辉中,,0,0,0,,but often it feels as though it's jarring and out of nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.75,0:15:21.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,But don't worry, we're going to get to some very egregious examples of this later on in the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.30,0:15:26.13,辉中,,0,0,0,,All that's really important to understand is that Ellie and Dina shared a first kiss,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.13,0:15:32.73,辉中,,0,0,0,,a character that we meet briefly, said something offensive and bigoted,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.73,0:15:35.61,辉中,,0,0,0,,and everybody wants you to know that it's bigoted.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.61,0:15:40.11,辉中,,0,0,0,,You get some sandwiches and then you go off to start on patrol.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.11,0:15:43.64,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's also important to understand that Jesse just broke up with Dina
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.11,0:15:48.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,around a week to a week and a half before this is taking place.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.32,0:15:52.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,Or may be Dina broke up with him, or maybe it was mutual.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.05,0:15:57.51,辉中,,0,0,0,,I don't know, it … it's so high school …  these first few conversations. It's kind of painful.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.51,0:16:02.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,Jessie heads off to the stable to prepare the horses and the rest of the attendees.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.16,0:16:06.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,While Dina and Ellie shared a snowball fight against a bunch of kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.52,0:16:09.47,辉中,,0,0,0,,Now I kind of found this snowball fight to be a little weird
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.47,0:16:14.37,辉中,,0,0,0,,because it seemed as though it's meant to serve as some sort of combat introduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.37,0:16:19.38,辉中,,0,0,0,,But I think I was just reading too much into it because I don't think it does a very good job of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.38,0:16:22.17,辉中,,0,0,0,,Now I did go back through the game a second time,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.17,0:16:27.39,辉中,,0,0,0,,as I stated previously on "New Game +" and on the hardest difficulty.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.39,0:16:32.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,After becoming completely familiarized with the controls after playing the entire game,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.07,0:16:37.15,辉中,,0,0,0,,this whole snowball fight was much more intriguing and interesting and frankly fun
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.15,0:16:39.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,than it was the first time I played.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.12,0:16:43.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,The three tiered stance that Ellie's able to have between standing, crouch and prone
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.90,0:16:46.47,辉中,,0,0,0,,is something that takes a minute to get used to.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.47,0:16:51.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,I know it sounds weird because that's true of pretty much any third person or first person shooter
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.90,0:16:53.85,辉中,,0,0,0,,that they're going to have those three stances.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.85,0:16:59.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,But in TLOU2, there are multiple levels of movement associated with each.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.25,0:17:00.48,辉中,,0,0,0,,And that's more of my point.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.48,0:17:05.58,辉中,,0,0,0,,The sequence does a very poor job of introducing the player to those three stances.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.58,0:17:10.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,But you are able to use each of those three stances in this sequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.32,0:17:11.79,辉中,,0,0,0,,It just seems a little jarring,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.79,0:17:15.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,but I will admit I appreciate the effort that they put into this
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.56,0:17:18.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,because it's still way better than the alternative,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.45,0:17:22.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,which would be to have the standard stereotypical sequence
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.68,0:17:26.58,辉中,,0,0,0,,where the protagonist goes and has shown how to use a gun,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.58,0:17:31.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,and it's like issue bottles or some crabs …  I hate that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.35,0:17:36.57,辉中,,0,0,0,,Probably the most egregious example would be the opening of Fallout 3 when you're given a BB gun,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.57,0:17:41.94,辉中,,0,0,0,,and then you go downstairs, shoot some targets and then some giant radroaches.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.94,0:17:44.46,辉中,,0,0,0,,I just think that that's so overplayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.46,0:17:47.58,辉中,,0,0,0,,If you're going to introduce shooting mechanics and combat,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.58,0:17:50.94,辉中,,0,0,0,,you should at the very least have a little bit of a creative spin to it,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.94,0:17:56.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,so I appreciate that throwing compacted snow at children was presented here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.00,0:17:58.98,辉中,,0,0,0,,After hucking some powder you meet up with Dina,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.98,0:18:03.36,辉中,,0,0,0,,there's some awkward exchanges where Ellie isn't sure how to talk to …
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.36,0:18:05.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,I mean again, it … it's very high school.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.34,0:18:09.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,The two walks out the stables and you head out on patrol.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.00,0:18:12.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,Then the first surprise of the game hits,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.33,0:18:15.99,辉中,,0,0,0,,and to be honest, it's a surprise, even if you had the game spoiled for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.99,0:18:20.67,辉中,,0,0,0,,You see the camera slowly pans over a bunch of sleeping young adults.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.67,0:18:27.93,辉中,,0,0,0,,It centers on one girl who most of us will immediately recognize from the Paris Games trailer from 2017,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.93,0:18:31.53,辉中,,0,0,0,,she gets up talks to a young man who asks to show her something,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.53,0:18:34.02,辉中,,0,0,0,,and then we are given control of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.02,0:18:36.75,辉中,,0,0,0,,Like I said earlier, I had the game spoiled for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.75,0:18:42.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,But all of those spoilers said that you were going to get to play half of the game as Abby
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.35,0:18:44.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,and start halfway through.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.34,0:18:48.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,I did not expect to be playing as her within the first 30 to 45 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.81,0:18:52.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,I bet you, at this point, some people had put the game down.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.05,0:18:55.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,After all, there was a very vocal minority that said
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.25,0:19:00.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,that they were going to flip out if you didn't play the whole game as Ellie and or Joel.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.12,0:19:03.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,But a key thing to understand here is that the player must give it time and effort
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.84,0:19:06.51,辉中,,0,0,0,,to stand on its own and justify itself
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.51,0:19:10.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,in the same way that you can't judge a book by its cover or a film by its trailer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.29,0:19:14.91,辉中,,0,0,0,,You'll never get an informed opinion of the game if you don't give it a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.91,0:19:19.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,This isn't to say that you have to play every single game in order to have an opinion of every single game,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.29,0:19:24.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,but rather that if you're going to have an extremely negative or critical opinion of a game,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.18,0:19:26.91,辉中,,0,0,0,,you have to be able to justify that critical opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.91,0:19:31.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,And in my opinion, I don't think it's fair to say that playing as any character
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.44,0:19:37.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,other than the one on the Box-Art is bad bad and means that the game is terrible and not worth your time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.07,0:19:40.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,After you take control of Abby and you start exploring through the woods,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.77,0:19:43.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,walking through some pretty deep snow,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.08,0:19:45.27,辉中,,0,0,0,,seeing some interesting landscapes,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.27,0:19:48.93,辉中,,0,0,0,,these two characters share in some dialogue about other people in the group,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.93,0:19:51.65,辉中,,0,0,0,,likely the same people that you just saw the camera pan over.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.65,0:19:56.31,辉中,,0,0,0,,Now we don't know any of these people at this point and Naughty Dog will do this a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.31,0:20:00.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,They are unapologetic in their unexplained dialogue.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.18,0:20:03.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,The characters will have conversations that makes sense to them,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.21,0:20:08.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,but might not, or perhaps don't make any sense at all to the player.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.82,0:20:10.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,Now I love this,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.08,0:20:15.27,辉中,,0,0,0,,though I do admit that it can be confusing to those who like to enjoy their content more passively.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.17,0:20:17.55,辉中,,0,0,0,,But this is a narrative game,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.55,0:20:21.54,辉中,,0,0,0,,it seems like it comes with the territory of this type of game to have dialogue
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.54,0:20:23.36,辉中,,0,0,0,,that's much more realistic and grounded
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.36,0:20:26.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,compared to dialogue that just hit you over the head with exposition.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.70,0:20:32.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,I also think it's important to note that these conversations make a second run of the game AWESOME.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.35,0:20:34.86,辉中,,0,0,0,,Seriously, every single thing they are discussing here,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.86,0:20:38.24,辉中,,0,0,0,,it makes perfect sense and is relatable and understandable.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.24,0:20:42.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,Once you've gone through the whole game and met all of these characters
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.12,0:20:46.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,and grown to know them and care about them throughout the course of the story,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.62,0:20:51.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,and as somebody that usually placed their games that I critique at least two times,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.72,0:20:54.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,I really appreciated this because it made it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.18,0:20:59.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,So my second run through was more informed and more interesting than my first run through.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.78,0:21:03.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,Really, I think you should play the game a second time through just to give it a shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.72,0:21:08.64,辉中,,0,0,0,,I think you'll be surprised at how many little things were added that you didn't hear before.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.64,0:21:10.48,辉中,,0,0,0,,But for the sake of a first run through,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.48,0:21:15.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,it's important to note that Abbey and Owen are the names of these two characters,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.18,0:21:18.15,辉中,,0,0,0,,they seem to have a previous relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.15,0:21:23.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,In other words, they dated at some sort of romantic involvement at some point.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.07,0:21:30.69,辉中,,0,0,0,,And also that some girl named Mel, who Owen is apparently involved with at this point, is pregnant.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.69,0:21:32.37,辉中,,0,0,0,,There may be, I'm all alone in this,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.37,0:21:36.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,but the second I heard she was pregnant, I got a pit in my stomach.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.90,0:21:40.92,辉中,,0,0,0,,This is what I meant when I tweeted out early in my first run through of the game
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.92,0:21:44.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,that I felt as though the opening was dreadful.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.85,0:21:50.37,辉中,,0,0,0,,I meant it in the purest sense of the word that the game fills you with dread.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.37,0:21:55.17,辉中,,0,0,0,,You have a sinking feeling in your stomach that something terrible is about to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.17,0:21:59.61,辉中,,0,0,0,,and I don't know if it's just that the game was spoiled and so everybody saw this coming,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.61,0:22:05.76,辉中,,0,0,0,,or that it's some sort of masterful way that they designed all of these conversations and scenes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.76,0:22:09.36,辉中,,0,0,0,,that makes you feel as though there's an impending danger and doom.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.36,0:22:10.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,I don't know which it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.80,0:22:17.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,I would love to hear your opinion of it down in the comments section below or tweeted at me @LukeStephensTV.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.07,0:22:23.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,But nonetheless I can't help but feel as though everything terrible that could happen is about to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.10,0:22:26.97,辉中,,0,0,0,,And so when I heard that this girl, Mel, was pregnant,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.97,0:22:31.24,辉中,,0,0,0,,I just knew something horrible was going to happen to her
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.24,0:22:37.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,and likely that one of the characters we were being introduced to on Ellie's side of the fence
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.08,0:22:41.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,would likely become pregnant to contrast the two relationships
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.12,0:22:45.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,and to set up narrative beats where you could have one character faced with an option,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.81,0:22:47.86,辉中,,0,0,0,,have the other character faced with the other option
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.86,0:22:51.15,辉中,,0,0,0,,and see how each reacts in their individual moments.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.15,0:22:55.95,辉中,,0,0,0,,But I understand that they likely doesn't make any sense at all if you haven't played through the game yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.95,0:22:59.22,辉中,,0,0,0,,so I'm simply going to move on and loop back to it later.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.22,0:23:00.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,I promise it'll make sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.70,0:23:04.65,辉中,,0,0,0,,Abby and Owen reach their destination, and they overlook Jackson.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.65,0:23:06.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's a massive city.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.45,0:23:12.30,辉中,,0,0,0,,And judging Abby's reaction, it seems as though she didn't expect it to be this massive at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.30,0:23:16.17,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's not clear what they're looking for, but it's a man for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.17,0:23:22.61,辉中,,0,0,0,,any one with two brain cells to rub together will instantly know that they're talking about and looking for Joel
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.61,0:23:25.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,though we don't know why at this particular moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.18,0:23:31.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,Now Owen doesn't think that they should continue on this quest to reach whoever they're looking for
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.08,0:23:36.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,because they obviously aren't going to be able to infiltrate Jackson no matter how hard they try.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.78,0:23:39.15,辉中,,0,0,0,,They're a small group and they aren't going to be able to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.15,0:23:41.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,So he thinks that they should just turn back.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.52,0:23:45.76,辉中,,0,0,0,,Especially since malaise now pregnant, they need to return to take care of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.76,0:23:48.66,辉中,,0,0,0,,Again remember this plot point,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.66,0:23:56.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,Owen, the dude, wants to turn back to make sure that he can take care of the woman that he impregnated.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.34,0:23:59.64,辉中,,0,0,0,,It seems like a weird, random thing to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.64,0:24:03.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,But this is something that's going to be repeated later in the story,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.06,0:24:08.99,辉中,,0,0,0,,and Ellie is going to be making the same decision that Abby makes in this moment, a stupid one.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.99,0:24:12.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,Naughty Dog will do this a lot throughout the course of the main story
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.92,0:24:17.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,where they will have Abby do something and then change it with a fresh coat of paint
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.18,0:24:20.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,and have Ellie do the same exact thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.20,0:24:24.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,But you can't help feel as though Ellie is more justified in her actions,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.84,0:24:28.23,辉中,,0,0,0,,while Abbey is just a bad villainess character.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.23,0:24:30.30,辉中,,0,0,0,,This game is all about perspectives
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.30,0:24:36.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,and this flip flopping that they do constantly is an important piece of that narrative mechanism.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.00,0:24:38.37,辉中,,0,0,0,,Now I'll be obviously doesn't want to turn back.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.37,0:24:44.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,They've travelled, presumably for days, weeks and even months to get to where they are now
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.06,0:24:48.66,辉中,,0,0,0,,and simply to turn around upon seeing the city of Jackson.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.66,0:24:50.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,It doesn't seem like it's a good option.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.40,0:24:53.64,辉中,,0,0,0,,Owen says that they should return back to the mansion they're staying at.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.64,0:24:56.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,But Abby doesn't like their recommendation,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.70,0:25:02.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,and she starts to become enraged, and she pushes on herself towards Jackson,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.34,0:25:06.65,辉中,,0,0,0,,trying to find a patrol that was traveling that Owen spotted
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.65,0:25:09.75,辉中,,0,0,0,,in order to get them to tell her where their target is,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.75,0:25:14.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,so that she can finish the job herself before returning back to wherever they came from.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.41,0:25:17.73,辉中,,0,0,0,,Controlling Abby, you push forward into an impending storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.73,0:25:22.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,You fight some zombies and you eventually find some tracks from one of the patrols.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.32,0:25:29.43,辉中,,0,0,0,,These patrols are the same ones that characters such as Ellie, Dina, Jesse, Joel and Tommy are all on,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.43,0:25:36.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,and this is the first of a plethora of coincidences in the early hours of the game that set up its narrative,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.18,0:25:39.53,辉中,,0,0,0,,the coincidence that Abby happened to be driven into a rage
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.53,0:25:42.99,辉中,,0,0,0,,at the same time that Joel and everyone else happens to be out on patrol.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.99,0:25:44.55,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's going to happen a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.55,0:25:47.22,辉中,,0,0,0,,Joel is an old man as his Tommy,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.22,0:25:52.02,辉中,,0,0,0,,at the very least older than all the youngsters that they have out on the patrols with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.02,0:25:57.48,辉中,,0,0,0,,The fact that Joel is still going on patrols is, in my opinion, a bit of a stretch.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.48,0:26:02.73,辉中,,0,0,0,,It would be stupid for him to go on patrols, especially because he has a leadership position within the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.73,0:26:06.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,His super fancy house, I think, serves as proof positive of that,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.96,0:26:11.61,辉中,,0,0,0,,Not to mention that Tommy, his brother, who was also going out on patrols with him,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.61,0:26:14.85,辉中,,0,0,0,,has a leadership position within the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.85,0:26:17.85,辉中,,0,0,0,,In many ways, Tommy runs the city along with his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.85,0:26:23.22,辉中,,0,0,0,,So to me, it just seems like a bit of a stretch that Tommy and Joel would be going out on patrols at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.22,0:26:28.92,辉中,,0,0,0,,But I understand that perhaps Joel or Tommy just want to get out and get their hands dirty.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.92,0:26:33.27,辉中,,0,0,0,,They don't want to feel old, they don't want to feel as though they can't contribute,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.27,0:26:35.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,so they want to go out and do things themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.25,0:26:38.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,I understand that perhaps that's justifiable.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.52,0:26:42.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,But I can't help feel as though Joel and Tommy being out on patrols
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.16,0:26:46.65,辉中,,0,0,0,,the same patrol routes that Ellie Dina and Jesse are taking,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.65,0:26:50.98,辉中,,0,0,0,,was purely designed, and established that way to make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.98,0:26:57.60,辉中,,0,0,0,,that Abby would be able to encounter Joel and Tommy while she randomly ran through the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.60,0:27:01.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,And this is the reason that I don't like narrative coincidences.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.32,0:27:03.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,Often it's just to give a way
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.21,0:27:09.27,辉中,,0,0,0,,that the writers are trying to force characters into normally unjustifiable situations.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.27,0:27:11.58,辉中,,0,0,0,,But it's not always a bad thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.58,0:27:16.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,In fact, in some cases, I think these coincidences can lead to some really interesting sequences.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.80,0:27:19.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,I mean, look at that scene from Breaking Bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.29,0:27:23.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,Where Jane's father runs into vault at a bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.25,0:27:27.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,They share a short conversation about fatherhood, about kids,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.90,0:27:33.87,辉中,,0,0,0,,and they don't realize that they're talking about two characters, in this case, Jesse and Jane,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.87,0:27:39.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,who are inextricably tied and who are about to go on a roller coaster together.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.40,0:27:44.01,辉中,,0,0,0,,For those of you who have seen the show and know what happens right after this meeting,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.01,0:27:48.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,you are going to probably think roller coaster is a bit of an understatement.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.12,0:27:50.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,But didn't I didn't want to spoil it? So …
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.76,0:27:53.01,辉中,,0,0,0,,The point is, go watch Breaking Bad, it's awesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.01,0:27:57.24,辉中,,0,0,0,,The other point is that narrative coincidences can be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.24,0:28:02.46,辉中,,0,0,0,,After all, coincidences do happen in real life all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.46,0:28:08.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,The problem comes when they are used to make characters do things they wouldn't otherwise be doing
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.05,0:28:11.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,in order to fulfill some sort of plot point.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.34,0:28:17.67,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's the same reason I hate psychics or prophecies in stories because I think that they're just lazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.67,0:28:20.94,辉中,,0,0,0,,The writers know that they want a character to go and do something,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.94,0:28:25.53,辉中,,0,0,0,,so they write some sort of prophecy to explain how it's going to happen,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.53,0:28:29.13,辉中,,0,0,0,,and then they make sure that they have characters that fit around that prophecy.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.13,0:28:30.24,辉中,,0,0,0,,And if it's a little messy,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.24,0:28:36.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,or if it doesn't seem to be totally justified narratively or in terms of the characters, motivations,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.06,0:28:40.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,they simply explain it by way of while he or she was fulfilling the prophecy.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.41,0:28:41.61,辉中,,0,0,0,,It had to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.61,0:28:44.73,辉中,,0,0,0,,It must have happened because the prophecy stated.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.73,0:28:46.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's just lazy,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.20,0:28:50.79,辉中,,0,0,0,,And while I feel as though many of the instances of coincidences in TLOU2,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.79,0:28:55.53,辉中,,0,0,0,,are not justifiable and are a grievous offences,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.53,0:29:00.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,I think that other instances are more justifiable and could be explained.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.33,0:29:04.95,辉中,,0,0,0,,But eventually there becomes so many that stack up on top of each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.95,0:29:09.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,It just seems as though Naughty Dog need Joel to run into Abby,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.21,0:29:13.17,辉中,,0,0,0,,and this was the fastest, cleanest way that they could figure out how to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.17,0:29:17.13,辉中,,0,0,0,,In a previous episode of NitGrit, a show that I do here on Youtube,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.13,0:29:21.60,辉中,,0,0,0,,I discussed narrative coincidences in TLOU2,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.60,0:29:27.75,辉中,,0,0,0,,and I couldn't help but notice that they were all front loaded in the opening hour or two of TLOU2.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.75,0:29:32.13,辉中,,0,0,0,,I threw out a potential intro that they could have swapped where, for instance,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.13,0:29:35.46,辉中,,0,0,0,,Abby, Owen and perhaps a few other members of her crew
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.46,0:29:39.88,辉中,,0,0,0,,infiltrated Jackson working with the people being welcomed in
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.88,0:29:44.92,辉中,,0,0,0,,and eventually earning the trust of Joel and Tommy, and Ellie
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.92,0:29:49.53,辉中,,0,0,0,,until eventually they turned on everybody, killed Joel and escape in the middle of the night,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.53,0:29:53.19,辉中,,0,0,0,,while the game then carries out just like it would have otherwise,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.19,0:29:58.23,辉中,,0,0,0,,it could have been really interesting because Abby and Ellie could have even formed a friendship,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.23,0:30:02.61,辉中,,0,0,0,,or at least some sort of sympathetic position towards each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.61,0:30:05.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,which would have made the betrayal all the worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.07,0:30:08.76,辉中,,0,0,0,,I mean, as of right now, Tommy and Joel are very welcoming to this group.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.76,0:30:12.88,辉中,,0,0,0,,They even invite them back to Jackson to restock on supplies before leaving
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.88,0:30:16.98,辉中,,0,0,0,,right before you know the thing happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.98,0:30:19.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,So we know that Tommy and Joel are welcoming.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.35,0:30:22.17,辉中,,0,0,0,,They would have brought this group in, at least for a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.17,0:30:23.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,Perhaps if they came in,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.70,0:30:29.94,辉中,,0,0,0,,they pretended to be wandering survivors simply in need of assistance in a new fresh start.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.94,0:30:33.42,辉中,,0,0,0,,Perhaps then they go when they work at Jackson for a few weeks,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.42,0:30:38.85,辉中,,0,0,0,,Or maybe even just a couple of days before turning and killing Joel and escaping.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.85,0:30:43.02,辉中,,0,0,0,,At the very least, then you don't have to rely on a bunch of coincidences.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.02,0:30:47.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,But I do understand that it might have been bad for pacing
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.35,0:30:52.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,and especially considering the leaks that happened towards the game's release.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.08,0:30:54.27,辉中,,0,0,0,,It seems as though is probably for the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.27,0:30:56.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,because once the game was spoiled,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.10,0:30:58.91,辉中,,0,0,0,,we all knew that Abby was going to kill Joel
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.91,0:31:05.67,辉中,,0,0,0,,so that would have completely negated the opening sequence where Abby and Ellie are starting to bond,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.67,0:31:08.67,辉中,,0,0,0,,or perhaps at least tolerating each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.67,0:31:11.79,辉中,,0,0,0,,I've heard from various people on Twitter and through Email
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.79,0:31:15.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,that Naughty Dog was actually considering this as an opening,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.12,0:31:18.60,辉中,,0,0,0,,which is funny because I just let it roll off my dome,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.60,0:31:20.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,I wasn't actually thinking that hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.34,0:31:24.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,But apparently this was a seriously considered intro sequence
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.12,0:31:28.02,辉中,,0,0,0,,instead of what we got in the end product of TLOU2,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.02,0:31:35.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,But they decided to go in this current direction because the other version ran into a lot of pacing issues.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.25,0:31:40.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,In other words, you likely would have needed to spend the first five or six hours of the game in Jackson
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.80,0:31:46.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,doing menial chores while getting to know Abby and her crew before being betrayed,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.35,0:31:50.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,it would have completely changed the structure of the rest of the game,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.25,0:31:53.49,辉中,,0,0,0,,so Naughty Dog just decided to expedite the process,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.49,0:31:59.61,辉中,,0,0,0,,have Abby get to Joel within the first two hours of the game and get the revenge plot moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.61,0:32:00.75,辉中,,0,0,0,,I think that's fair.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.75,0:32:06.42,辉中,,0,0,0,,I just think it's a little sloppy, considering how many coincidences they rely on to make it happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.42,0:32:10.26,辉中,,0,0,0,,After Abby finds the tracks in the snow, leading to one of the patrols,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.26,0:32:13.65,辉中,,0,0,0,,we swap back to Ellie, whose on patrol with Dina.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.65,0:32:19.26,辉中,,0,0,0,,You ride your horses through a beautifully realized landscape, walking on ice in a river.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.26,0:32:20.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's absolutely beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.82,0:32:26.31,辉中,,0,0,0,,I mean again, how Naughty Dog achieves these graphical features, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.31,0:32:29.91,辉中,,0,0,0,,It really makes it look like every other development studio isn't even trying.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.91,0:32:33.75,辉中,,0,0,0,,There's a lot of character building in this sequence as you go on your patrol.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.75,0:32:38.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,There's some light flirting, clearly, Dina likes Ellie and Ellie likes Dina.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.82,0:32:41.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,And the tension starts to rise here.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.06,0:32:45.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,Again there's a lot of dread, things are going too well,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.45,0:32:51.19,辉中,,0,0,0,,and the world of TLOU, as we know, is very cutthroat, sometimes literally.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.19,0:32:56.58,辉中,,0,0,0,,The fact that everybody's happy that they are so carefree that they're even flirting with each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.58,0:33:01.14,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's unsettling, because we know that something bad has to happen soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.14,0:33:05.91,辉中,,0,0,0,,But you continue exploring, you go to an outpost to explore some abandoned houses.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.91,0:33:06.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,And at one point,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.96,0:33:13.02,辉中,,0,0,0,,Ellie even says that she's going to be inviting Joel over for a movie later that night.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.02,0:33:17.76,辉中,,0,0,0,,This will be VERY important at the end of the game,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.76,0:33:19.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,so make sure you remember this.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.56,0:33:26.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,Ellie on this day was planning on having Joel over for a movie that night.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.07,0:33:27.60,辉中,,0,0,0,,It seems like a small point,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.60,0:33:33.09,辉中,,0,0,0,,especially considering that Ellie and Joel have this deep connection with each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.09,0:33:37.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,She lives right behind him, even still in the grandmothers sweet,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.20,0:33:40.74,辉中,,0,0,0,,and it makes sense that perhaps they would try to fill an empty time,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.74,0:33:42.60,辉中,,0,0,0,,watching movies and spending time together.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.60,0:33:46.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,But again, at the end of the game, we're going to find out a lot more.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.29,0:33:51.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,And this very statement by Ellie something that happens as an optional moment
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.32,0:33:53.46,辉中,,0,0,0,,while you're exploring an abandoned house.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.30,0:33:56.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,This is going to be very important.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.10,0:33:59.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,Ellie and Dina, come up on a supermarket that's infested.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.07,0:34:03.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,You cleared out, gives you the chance to explore some stealth options and combat,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.84,0:34:07.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,and it's a good thing that this is a really well done portion of the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.44,0:34:10.76,辉中,,0,0,0,,Because this stealth and the crafting that goes along with it
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.76,0:34:13.71,辉中,,0,0,0,,is going to be the bread and butter of the game,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.71,0:34:16.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,especially if you're playing on higher difficulties,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.05,0:34:20.55,辉中,,0,0,0,,you're going to need to get acclimated to these mechanics as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.55,0:34:23.61,辉中,,0,0,0,,You are also given a quick introduction to clickers as well,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.61,0:34:27.39,辉中,,0,0,0,,and these guys work almost identically to how they did in the first game.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.39,0:34:31.86,辉中,,0,0,0,,I don't really feel the need to explain a lot as to how these sequences work,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.86,0:34:36.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,because if you've played the first game, you're going to know how this goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.00,0:34:39.57,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's going to be a hot minute before we're thrown anything that's markedly different.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.57,0:34:41.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,I will say that in the first game,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.25,0:34:45.91,辉中,,0,0,0,,it always bugging me that clickers are obviously able to navigate their environments
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.91,0:34:51.27,辉中,,0,0,0,,by use of clicking sounds that use echolocation to map out their environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.27,0:34:55.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,However, they never were able to hear characters talking to each other
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.40,0:34:59.88,辉中,,0,0,0,,or you reloading your weapon or moving your backpack on and off.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.88,0:35:06.36,辉中,,0,0,0,,That is mostly true again in this game, except only on the lower levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.36,0:35:11.43,辉中,,0,0,0,,In my testing, I actually found that on new game Plus on survivor difficulty,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.43,0:35:13.98,辉中,,0,0,0,,the clickers can actually hear this as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.98,0:35:18.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,If you open your backpack to swap weapons, they'll notice and they'll come running.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.96,0:35:22.89,辉中,,0,0,0,,This was a game changer in terms of immersion.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.89,0:35:28.53,辉中,,0,0,0,,Seriously, I've never played a game where I was so attentive to everything that I was doing,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.53,0:35:31.74,辉中,,0,0,0,,that I was scared to even open up the inventory,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.74,0:35:37.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,because I knew that it was going to create a small amount of sound that could attract clickers,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.56,0:35:40.36,辉中,,0,0,0,,which could mean that I die and have to reload.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.36,0:35:43.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,Granted to some people, I'm sure that sounds absolutely terrible,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.44,0:35:46.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,which is why there are difficulty settings to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.08,0:35:49.47,辉中,,0,0,0,,But if you want to be totally immersed in this game,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.47,0:35:52.92,辉中,,0,0,0,,I recommend you play it on the hardest possible difficulty.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.92,0:35:54.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,It really does change everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.90,0:35:57.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,Another thing to note in this supermarket sequences that
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.68,0:36:01.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,Ellie is wearing a mask when she encounters spores now.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.32,0:36:02.43,辉中,,0,0,0,,If you played the first game,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.43,0:36:07.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,this is going to be kind of weird because obviously Ellie is immune to the virus,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.41,0:36:10.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,or so we thought, why does she need to wear a mask?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.41,0:36:12.66,辉中,,0,0,0,,In the trailers we saw before the game's launch,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.66,0:36:16.11,辉中,,0,0,0,,a lot of people thought that this would mean that Ellie was no longer immune,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.11,0:36:20.49,辉中,,0,0,0,,or perhaps she was not as immune as she once was,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.49,0:36:24.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,so perhaps if she inhaled spores, that would make her very very sick,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.06,0:36:25.74,辉中,,0,0,0,,but she would eventually pull through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.74,0:36:28.02,辉中,,0,0,0,,However, the explanation is far simpler.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.02,0:36:33.69,辉中,,0,0,0,,Joel and Ellie obviously know that Ellie is immune, but nobody else can know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.69,0:36:35.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,If people were to find out that Ellie's immune,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.82,0:36:39.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,the same crap with the fireflies would happen all over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.72,0:36:43.71,辉中,,0,0,0,,Now this seems to be much more Joel's wish than it is Ellie's,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.71,0:36:51.09,辉中,,0,0,0,,after all, Ellie was totally prepared and fine with giving her life to save humanity in the form of a vaccine,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.09,0:36:53.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,And this would of course make sense because Joel wanted to make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.84,0:36:58.53,辉中,,0,0,0,,nobody else would come to Ellie to try and capitalize on her gift,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.53,0:37:01.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,because if they did, it would mean that he would lose her.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.29,0:37:04.98,辉中,,0,0,0,,But the fact that Ellie is still using the mask, even though she doesn't need to,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.98,0:37:08.79,辉中,,0,0,0,,I think, serves as proof positive that she still cares about what he thinks,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.79,0:37:11.64,辉中,,0,0,0,,and she's yet to fully separate and become her own person.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.64,0:37:16.14,辉中,,0,0,0,,But this isn't something that's explained or really justified at this point in the game,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.14,0:37:22.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,but we will see an actual conversation between Ellie and Joel later on that explains all of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.32,0:37:27.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,If I throw a bunch of zombies and clickers and eventually find your way up to the top of the supermarket,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.33,0:37:29.58,辉中,,0,0,0,,where you jumped down out to the front,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.58,0:37:35.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,Ellie and Dina's entire goal throughout exploring this supermarket was to clear it of infected,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.16,0:37:36.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,and they've done just that.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.33,0:37:40.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,Honestly, it's not a bad way of forcing the player to kill zombies
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.12,0:37:44.01,辉中,,0,0,0,,in order to get experience with the combat system and become more comfortable with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.01,0:37:48.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,A lot of people are going to simply try to stealth around them in most instances,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.33,0:37:51.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,especially later in the game, when resources become very scarce.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.45,0:37:58.23,辉中,,0,0,0,,but if the characters mission is to wipe out all infected in an area to protect Jackson, the city,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.23,0:38:01.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,you all of a sudden don't have to worry about players doing that
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.04,0:38:05.46,辉中,,0,0,0,,because they're going to be justified narratively in killing absolutely everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.46,0:38:11.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,After all, they can't leave the area unless they've completely wiped all of the infected within that area.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.07,0:38:15.93,辉中,,0,0,0,,Once you get out of the supermarket, the blizzard starts to come in full force.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.93,0:38:21.66,辉中,,0,0,0,,So Ellie and Dina race through the snow, and end up at a library that Dina knew about.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.66,0:38:24.36,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's the previous abode of somebody named Eugene,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.36,0:38:28.50,辉中,,0,0,0,,who, by my calculations, using the log book in the first outpost,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.50,0:38:34.92,辉中,,0,0,0,,likely died of a stroke laid in the previous year just a few months before this game starts.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.92,0:38:38.31,辉中,,0,0,0,,Well, we know about him is that he was a firefly who served with Tommy,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.31,0:38:42.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,and he was also an electronics geek who was a total hippy.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.45,0:38:44.42,辉中,,0,0,0,,In other words, he loved weed.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.42,0:38:46.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,After being introduced to the workbench,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.32,0:38:54.50,辉中,,0,0,0,,Which has to be the most awesome and kick ass weapon customization system I have ever seen in a game
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.50,0:38:58.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,you went down to the basement where you find Eugene's true passion.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.68,0:39:00.15,辉中,,0,0,0,,Now, when I first saw all of this,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.15,0:39:07.17,辉中,,0,0,0,,I had to ask the question: Was he actually like selling this stuff? Was he trading it?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.17,0:39:09.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,I don't know, maybe there's a notes that I missed,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.21,0:39:12.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,that explained what he was doing with all of this pot.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.78,0:39:17.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,I don't know, let me know if there is something there probably is, and I just didn't find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.40,0:39:22.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,But it seems as though it's a huge potential opportunity for Jackson in terms of trade,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.56,0:39:27.36,辉中,,0,0,0,,if they had a whole of this marijuana to offer took transients coming in and out,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.36,0:39:29.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,I mean it would be pretty funny if Jackson,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.40,0:39:36.42,辉中,,0,0,0,,this thriving city in the apocalypse if their entire economy was based off of selling weed.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.42,0:39:39.76,辉中,,0,0,0,,I think it would be hilarious and kind of cool
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.76,0:39:44.58,辉中,,0,0,0,,that in this world, this one thing this plant has brought everybody together.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.58,0:39:46.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,I mean, yeah, I live in Colorado.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.35,0:39:50.13,辉中,,0,0,0,,Maybe that's why I'm partial to that argument.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.13,0:39:53.67,辉中,,0,0,0,,I mean I don't smoke and I don't … I don't smoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.80,0:39:58.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,But, still, like you live in Colorado, everyone talks about pot, and this is what you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.77,0:40:00.66,辉中,,0,0,0,,What was I talking about? Oh, yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.66,0:40:02.31,辉中,,0,0,0,,Dana and Ellie smoke a blunt.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.31,0:40:07.71,辉中,,0,0,0,,They shared some high school musical style discussion about their kiss from the night before.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.71,0:40:10.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,And then they share another one and then a few other ones,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.80,0:40:16.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,and eventually their overcome, and they begin making out as we cut to Abby, once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.62,0:40:18.51,辉中,,0,0,0,,she's running from all sorts of hordes.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.51,0:40:21.75,辉中,,0,0,0,,She's making a lot of noise, and they are definitely hearing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.75,0:40:26.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,This increases the tension a lot after the calm of the previous scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.04,0:40:28.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,And this type of pacing is going to happen often.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.29,0:40:29.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,Honestly, I love it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.70,0:40:31.50,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's a very common Naughty Dog tactic.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.50,0:40:36.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,They work you up, and then they contrast it with something that's very calm that lowers your heart rate
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.05,0:40:41.37,辉中,,0,0,0,,only to whack you over the head again and then luring you back into a sense of calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.37,0:40:44.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,The best example would be in the opening of the original game.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.52,0:40:46.59,辉中,,0,0,0,,Everything's calm and relaxed,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.59,0:40:50.88,辉中,,0,0,0,,And then the world starts to fall apart and everything's terrible and then your daughter dies,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.88,0:40:55.75,辉中,,0,0,0,,and then you cut forward to Joel sleeping on a mattress twenty years later
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.75,0:41:00.97,辉中,,0,0,0,,and having a very calm, comparatively conversation with Tess
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.97,0:41:06.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,and prepare your butts because this is going to happen on a regular basis throughout all of the sequel.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.18,0:41:11.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,And thankfully, the predictability of this doesn't actually negatively affect the efficacy of this mechanism.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.52,0:41:12.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,It still works pretty well.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.70,0:41:18.28,辉中,,0,0,0,,Now as you run as Abby through all of these hordes, you eventually reach a chain link fence.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.28,0:41:21.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,You squeeze through it and a bunch of zombies grab onto you,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.81,0:41:28.23,辉中,,0,0,0,,start ripping your hat off and doing all sorts of gross stuff, and then one breaks through,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.23,0:41:29.13,辉中,,0,0,0,,and this happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.44,0:41:48.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,Now they haven't been introduced yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.00,0:41:51.54,辉中,,0,0,0,,but as of right now, Abby's just glad to be alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.54,0:41:52.92,辉中,,0,0,0,,As far as she knows,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.92,0:41:55.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,Joel is just some random guy, as is Tommy,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.80,0:41:59.71,辉中,,0,0,0,,and they just happened to be in the right place at the right time to save her.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.71,0:42:01.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,Again, a coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.32,0:42:04.75,辉中,,0,0,0,,This one's a little harder to justify and explained.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.75,0:42:10.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,Because they have no reason to be out at this dead end area of a building they have likely been in before.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.44,0:42:13.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,All of you escaped together to a ski lodge at the top of the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.68,0:42:14.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,You up on some horses,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.82,0:42:18.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,and after a brief introduction wherein Abby learns who she's with,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.96,0:42:23.55,辉中,,0,0,0,,she recommends that they weighed out the storm in a mansion that she and her friends have been staying in.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.55,0:42:26.98,辉中,,0,0,0,,Joel and Tommy agree to go without any significant hesitance
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.98,0:42:29.92,辉中,,0,0,0,,beyond the initial belief that they could survive in the lodge.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.05,0:42:32.55,辉中,,0,0,0,,Once again, it's another coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.55,0:42:34.49,辉中,,0,0,0,,Joel and Tommy, aren't this naive,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.49,0:42:39.27,辉中,,0,0,0,,or at the very least they shouldn't be, even when pushed in these extreme conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.27,0:42:42.27,辉中,,0,0,0,,我的意思是我明白外面暴风雪肆虐\NWhat I mean is, I understand that there's a blizzard raging,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.27,0:42:47.49,辉中,,0,0,0,,我也明白这会让他们做出相比天气晴好的时候不会做出的选择\Nand I understand that would push them into choices that they wouldn't otherwise make,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.49,0:42:49.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,我也明白这会让他们做出相比天气晴好的时候不会做出的选择\Nshould the weather be fine and dandy.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.35,0:42:53.49,辉中,,0,0,0,,But Joel and Tommy aren't stupid, and they know not to trust strangers,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.49,0:42:58.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,even a stranger that looks as innocent as hulked out heroin.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.44,0:43:03.51,辉中,,0,0,0,,and they definitely should know that they shouldn't trust a group of strangers
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.51,0:43:06.93,辉中,,0,0,0,,that are living out of a mansion that's on their patrol route.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.93,0:43:09.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,She says they've been staying there for a few days
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.20,0:43:14.22,辉中,,0,0,0,,that they have weapons, food and all sorts of things that could help Joel and Tommy.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.22,0:43:17.55,辉中,,0,0,0,,While it's nice that she's offering to help them in this way,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.55,0:43:23.22,辉中,,0,0,0,,it should also raise a lot of red flags that she's willing to help them first of all,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.22,0:43:30.15,辉中,,0,0,0,,and also that this giant group of people is present so close to Jackson without their knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.15,0:43:32.36,辉中,,0,0,0,,But nonetheless Joel and Tommy agree to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.36,0:43:36.93,辉中,,0,0,0,,Once you arrive at the cabin, Joel, Tommy, and Abby dismount and settle into the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.93,0:43:40.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,Abby is clearly distressed, while Tommy and Joel are none the wiser.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.81,0:43:47.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,Again, the dread is building. Something is very wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.16,0:43:52.01,辉中,,0,0,0,,Everyone moves into the nearby basement room, And Tommy and Joel introduce themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.01,0:43:56.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,Again, this might be construed as out of character
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.08,0:43:58.65,辉中,,0,0,0,,that they would use their real names to a bunch of strangers.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.65,0:44:01.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,But in my opinion, it's not actually stretch
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.29,0:44:06.03,辉中,,0,0,0,,because Tommy and Joel have no reason to believe that their first names could give them away,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.03,0:44:09.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,or that one of them is being hunted for that matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.18,0:44:12.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,Yes, they've all done a lot of really messed up stuff,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.18,0:44:17.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,but knowing somebody's first name and hunting them down across the country,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.40,0:44:19.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,that seems like a bit of a stretch.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.20,0:44:20.39,辉中,,0,0,0,,But here we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.39,0:44:24.88,辉中,,0,0,0,,Point is I don't think that it's unrealistic that Joel and Tommy use their real names
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.88,0:44:28.71,辉中,,0,0,0,,when introducing themselves to a group that seemingly is helping them out.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.71,0:44:32.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,And I have to say it's pretty impressive at how slow and steady
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.52,0:44:38.55,辉中,,0,0,0,,the dread is building throughout this entire introductory sequence, the prologue of the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.55,0:44:39.87,辉中,,0,0,0,,And then at this very moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.87,0:44:47.91,辉中,,0,0,0,,when Joel says his name and everybody's faces turn from very friendly to cold and evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.91,0:44:50.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's a moment that I'm not sure I'll ever forget
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.41,0:44:54.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,the second Joel says his name, the room shifts.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.18,0:44:56.36,辉中,,0,0,0,,You could hear a pin drop.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.36,0:45:01.53,辉中,,0,0,0,,Instead of being friendly, they all looked at him as though their hyenas looking at their next meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.53,0:45:07.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,And it's important to note that this kindness that we feel before Joel introduces himself
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.00,0:45:11.97,辉中,,0,0,0,,is very important and it will come up again later, I promise you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.97,0:45:15.92,辉中,,0,0,0,,Now Joel picks up on this shift, and this plays out.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.63,0:47:48.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,We cut back to Ellie, closing in on the cabin.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.06,0:47:52.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,Now right before Joel and Tommy pushed up to the cabin with Abby,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.29,0:48:01.26,辉中,,0,0,0,,We saw Jesse come across Abby and Dina in the basement of Eugene's library in a compromised position.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.26,0:48:06.48,辉中,,0,0,0,,He tells them that Joel and Tommy are missing and nobody has seen them since the storm came in.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.48,0:48:10.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,Ellie becomes panicked and races off to help find them.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.35,0:48:13.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's important to note also that Ellie stressed
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.41,0:48:17.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,that they should all split up to try and cover as much ground as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.16,0:48:19.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,Some people have said that this itself is a coincidence
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.72,0:48:22.37,辉中,,0,0,0,,or a bit of a stretch that they wouldn't actually do this,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.37,0:48:23.94,辉中,,0,0,0,,but again, think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.94,0:48:26.73,辉中,,0,0,0,,From her perspective, I don't think it's a stretch.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.73,0:48:28.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,Because as far as Ellie is concerned,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.56,0:48:33.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,it's very possible that Joel and Tommy simply had to bunker down somewhere because of the blizzard
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.80,0:48:36.27,辉中,,0,0,0,,and were caught there by surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.27,0:48:42.15,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's not to say that she expected Joel to be hunted by some random chick from Seattle.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.15,0:48:46.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,But regardless everybody breaks off looking for Joel and Tommy.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.05,0:48:50.37,辉中,,0,0,0,,After Abby starts her attack on Joel, we cut to Ellie, closing in on the cabin,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.37,0:48:54.54,辉中,,0,0,0,,they give a bit of a fake out here by dropping some ammo right as you enter the cabin,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.54,0:48:56.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,which makes the player think that you're about to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.70,0:48:58.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,I actually really like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.08,0:49:00.09,辉中,,0,0,0,,When games do this, do this little fake out.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.09,0:49:01.14,辉中,,0,0,0,,So you're prepped for a fight,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.14,0:49:04.23,辉中,,0,0,0,,and then it's taken away from you, but I know that's just me.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.23,0:49:08.85,辉中,,0,0,0,,Of course this is in the case because the second that we enter the basement, this happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.15,0:51:19.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,There are some heated discussion between the members of Abby's party as to what to do with Ellie.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.44,0:51:22.14,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's all very muffled, and you can't understand any of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.14,0:51:24.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,though we will get to see this from another perspective later.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.90,0:51:26.73,辉中,,0,0,0,,Eventually they just knocked her out.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.73,0:51:30.94,辉中,,0,0,0,,and Ellie wakes up after some time to Dina and Jesse rescuing them.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.94,0:51:35.76,辉中,,0,0,0,,At this point is not clear if Tommy survived, but it's clear that Joel did not.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.39,0:51:51.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,You know what? This is as good a time as any to address the elephant in the room dead on the floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.12,0:51:52.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,I had the game spoiled for me,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.41,0:51:55.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,so I knew that Joel was going to die at some point.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.56,0:51:56.37,辉中,,0,0,0,,And to be honest,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.37,0:52:01.83,辉中,,0,0,0,,many of us had a feeling as though Joel was going to die at some point in the game years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.83,0:52:03.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,because they only made sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.72,0:52:08.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,One of the stereotypes of a sequel is that they're going to kill off one of the major characters
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.44,0:52:11.91,辉中,,0,0,0,,from the first iteration of whatever is in question,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.91,0:52:15.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,whether it's a movie and novel, a podcast or a video game,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.52,0:52:18.59,辉中,,0,0,0,,time and time again, we've seen this trope played out.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.59,0:52:22.17,辉中,,0,0,0,,And it's become a trope because this actually works pretty well.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.17,0:52:27.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,You grow the character and the audience falls in love with them over the course of the first story.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.00,0:52:30.86,辉中,,0,0,0,,Then, with this foundation laid you pull the rug out from everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.86,0:52:34.26,辉中,,0,0,0,,and smack them over the head with a two by four of emotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.26,0:52:38.46,辉中,,0,0,0,,Or maybe in this case, a golf club of emotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.46,0:52:40.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,Maybe that's too soon, I don't care, moving on.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.62,0:52:46.23,辉中,,0,0,0,,Even with this presumption, having been established by many people before this game was launched,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.23,0:52:50.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,Naughty Dog seems to have actively tried to dissuade fans from this presupposition
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.72,0:52:52.98,辉中,,0,0,0,,by way of their pre launch trailers.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.98,0:52:59.61,辉中,,0,0,0,,Now this actually got a lot of people pretty upset when they played through the entirety of TLOU2.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.61,0:53:02.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,There are multiple events that were shown in the trailers
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.72,0:53:06.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,that aren't actually indicative of what the game has to offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.45,0:53:08.86,辉中,,0,0,0,,The clearest example would be this one,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.86,0:53:12.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,where Ellie is fighting through a bunch of WLF,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.00,0:53:15.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,and then has a hand put over her mouth,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.00,0:53:18.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,and when she turns round, she sees that it's Joel,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.06,0:53:21.39,辉中,,0,0,0,,telling her that he's not going to let her do this by herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.39,0:53:24.59,辉中,,0,0,0,,Now I'm not going to respond in the same way that a lot of people on Twitter responded
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.59,0:53:27.42,辉中,,0,0,0,,where they demanded their money back to the false advertising.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.42,0:53:28.86,辉中,,0,0,0,,I don't think that's fair,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.86,0:53:32.99,辉中,,0,0,0,,especially because you paid sixty dollars and have gotten a lot of game play out of it before.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.99,0:53:36.66,辉中,,0,0,0,,You know, I don't even need to explain my reasoning, I just think that's stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.66,0:53:39.42,辉中,,0,0,0,,What I will say, however, was that this was very confusing,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.42,0:53:42.09,辉中,,0,0,0,,at least for me, the first time I play through the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.09,0:53:44.85,辉中,,0,0,0,,Having watched all of the trailers multiple times,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.85,0:53:50.43,辉中,,0,0,0,,I knew that Joel made an appearance later on in the game because Ellie responds to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.43,0:53:53.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,But that never happens in the actual game.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.70,0:53:57.69,辉中,,0,0,0,,So I kept asking myself whether or not there was going to be some sort of dream sequence
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.69,0:54:00.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,where she plays back through the same level again.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.33,0:54:05.13,辉中,,0,0,0,,But this time Joel is at the end of the line instead, and then that scene plays out.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.13,0:54:08.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,Of course, I don't have to tell you that never happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.25,0:54:11.86,辉中,,0,0,0,,This was simply a way to divert the attention from the fans
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.86,0:54:14.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,away from what was actually going to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.16,0:54:16.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,And Naughty Dog does have a history of doing this type of thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.68,0:54:18.99,辉中,,0,0,0,,which is part of the reason I can't fault them completely,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.99,0:54:20.64,辉中,,0,0,0,,because usually it's for a good reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.64,0:54:23.58,辉中,,0,0,0,,The most obvious example would be with the original TLOU,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.58,0:54:27.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,when they said that you would only be playing his Joel throughout the entirety of the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.45,0:54:29.91,辉中,,0,0,0,,Of course, this isn't true.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.91,0:54:32.97,辉中,,0,0,0,,And it made it so when you actually get your hands on Ellie,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.97,0:54:36.03,辉中,,0,0,0,,that sounded weird when I said it out loud,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.03,0:54:38.85,辉中,,0,0,0,,it made it, so when you started playing as alley,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.85,0:54:45.39,辉中,,0,0,0,,the entire sequence was much more surreal because you didn't expect at all to have this opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.39,0:54:47.49,辉中,,0,0,0,,Another example would be with this very game,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.49,0:54:53.28,辉中,,0,0,0,,TLOU2 when they said that you would only be playing as Elie throughout the entirety of the campaign,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.28,0:54:55.47,辉中,,0,0,0,,something which was obviously not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.47,0:55:00.85,辉中,,0,0,0,,The problem with these sort of white lies to better the game play experience for the player
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.85,0:55:04.48,辉中,,0,0,0,,is that they only work if people don't know any better.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.48,0:55:06.99,辉中,,0,0,0,,And with the original game, as far as I am aware,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.99,0:55:11.37,辉中,,0,0,0,,most people believed that you would only play as Joel throughout the entirety of the game,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.37,0:55:15.48,辉中,,0,0,0,,and it made it so when they got their hands on the controller playing as Ellie.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.48,0:55:19.98,辉中,,0,0,0,,It was much more interesting because they didn't expect it at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.98,0:55:25.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,But with TLOU2 and all of the leaks that followed, people saw this coming from a mile away,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.80,0:55:27.75,辉中,,0,0,0,,and it lost a lot of its punch.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.75,0:55:30.88,辉中,,0,0,0,,I've actually spent a lot of time thinking what this game would be like
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.88,0:55:34.83,辉中,,0,0,0,,if I had no expectations and nothing spoiled for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.83,0:55:37.23,辉中,,0,0,0,,I think the experience would have been much different,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.23,0:55:40.38,辉中,,0,0,0,,and I'm not sure how that would have changed my perspective.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.38,0:55:43.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,Nonetheless, if you happen to be one of the few lucky people
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.96,0:55:48.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,who got to play the entire game without having anything spoiled for you,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.00,0:55:52.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,I want to hear your thoughts down in the comment section below or in a tweet.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.04,0:55:56.73,辉中,,0,0,0,,Sent it to me, I'm really interested in hearing what your perspective is on all of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.73,0:56:01.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,But as for Joel's death itself, I have no problem with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.44,0:56:04.83,辉中,,0,0,0,,Joel's actions throughout the course of the first game were quite reckless
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.83,0:56:09.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,and he screwed over a lot of people and killed a lot of people while he was at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.84,0:56:14.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,I've said before, and I'll say it again: I don't think Joel is a hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.82,0:56:19.38,辉中,,0,0,0,,If anything, he's an anti hero, if you look at his actions in a vacuum.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.38,0:56:25.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,你完全可以说人生与道德在实际生活中会复杂得多\NYou can always say that life and morality is much more complicated than looking at it purely in a vacuum,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.08,0:56:31.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,但我仍然认为乔尔不能算是我们大家应该敬仰 应该向他学习的道德标杆\Nbut I think it still stands to say that Joel is not a pillar of morality,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.80,0:56:35.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,但我仍然认为乔尔不能算是我们大家应该敬仰 应该向他学习的道德标杆\Nto which we should all look and pray for guidance.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.70,0:56:42.55,辉中,,0,0,0,,I think rather, he's a damaged, broken, sad and a moral character
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.55,0:56:48.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,who is looking to do what he needs to do, to survive and protect those he cares about.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.06,0:56:51.51,辉中,,0,0,0,,That's something that I think is in a way admirable in and of itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.51,0:56:56.30,辉中,,0,0,0,,But I don't think that that makes you a hero quote-unquote in the same way
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.30,0:56:59.37,辉中,,0,0,0,,that you could compare a character such as Aloy
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.37,0:57:04.50,辉中,,0,0,0,,who is actively trying to do the moral thing in any instance that she comes across.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.50,0:57:08.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, from a game play perspective, we got our game with Joel.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.96,0:57:13.11,辉中,,0,0,0,,We know him, we have experienced him and his perspectives.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.11,0:57:15.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,I think it was time for something new,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.00,0:57:20.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,and if we had played through the entire game as Joel or half and half between Joel and Ellie,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.10,0:57:22.47,辉中,,0,0,0,,I think it would have lost a lot of its punch.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.47,0:57:27.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,Now Joel's death didn't come as a surprise to me. or probably any one,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.00,0:57:29.94,辉中,,0,0,0,,especially once you walk through that door in the cabin.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.94,0:57:36.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,That being said, it's still pretty horrible having to watch him get his head crammed in with a golf club.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.00,0:57:39.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's pretty haunting, but that's by design.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.12,0:57:44.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,Naughty Dog needed the player to be just as haunted by this event as Ellie is
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.04,0:57:47.31,辉中,,0,0,0,,because then they feel emotionally equivalent,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.31,0:57:50.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,especially in their hatred towards Abby,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.04,0:57:54.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,which is one of the major elements that they need to establish early on.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.81,0:58:00.03,辉中,,0,0,0,,You, the player, need to hate this girl with every fiber of your being.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.03,0:58:03.99,辉中,,0,0,0,,Just like Ellie hates her with every fibre of her being.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.99,0:58:08.88,辉中,,0,0,0,,so that later, when they try to flip perspectives and flip the table on you,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.88,0:58:10.92,辉中,,0,0,0,,they can do that effectively.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.92,0:58:12.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,If you're apathetic towards Abby
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.68,0:58:17.01,辉中,,0,0,0,,and then you go through the entirety of the game trying to pursue revenge,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.01,0:58:19.26,辉中,,0,0,0,,you're not going to be motivated at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.26,0:58:26.01,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's going to be pretty uninteresting because the entire premise of the game and the story is a moot point.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.01,0:58:32.37,辉中,,0,0,0,,But if you hate Abby, just as much as Elie hates her and wants to see her die,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.37,0:58:35.85,辉中,,0,0,0,,you'll be motivated to get through the first half of the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.85,0:58:39.87,辉中,,0,0,0,,And then Naughty Dog has you set up for the final act.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.87,0:58:42.60,辉中,,0,0,0,,Now, after this, we enter the end of the prologue.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.60,0:58:47.64,辉中,,0,0,0,,Yes, we are an hour into this video, and we are just getting out of the prologue.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.64,0:58:49.74,辉中,,0,0,0,,Ellie and Tommy discuss their next steps.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.74,0:58:53.43,辉中,,0,0,0,,Tommy talk to Maria, and she's not going to let him go or do anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.43,0:58:56.55,辉中,,0,0,0,,and he's not allowed to have any sort of spare men.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.55,0:58:58.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,He has to keep them all in Jackson.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.41,0:59:00.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,She thinks that they should just move on,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.18,0:59:03.99,辉中,,0,0,0,,except that what happened was terrible and go on with their lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.99,0:59:07.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,As usual, Maria seems to be the one voice of reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.08,0:59:10.23,辉中,,0,0,0,,Tommy and Ellie, however, are understandably upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.23,0:59:13.26,辉中,,0,0,0,,Tommy lost his brother in a terrible way,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.26,0:59:17.76,辉中,,0,0,0,,and Ellie also lost her "father figure" in a terrible way.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.76,0:59:20.22,辉中,,0,0,0,,They still aren't certain why this happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.22,0:59:25.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,or what Joel did that made them seek his death out so fervently.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.32,0:59:30.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,Tommy happened to see some patches on their coats that read "WLF".
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.00,0:59:32.79,辉中,,0,0,0,,And because of his previous history with the Fireflies,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.79,0:59:35.91,辉中,,0,0,0,,he knows that that would be the Washington Liberation Front,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.91,0:59:38.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,which is a group that's in Washington.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.40,0:59:39.54,辉中,,0,0,0,,Huh … Go figure.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.54,0:59:43.59,辉中,,0,0,0,,And that's what allows Ellie to know where she needs to go next.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.59,0:59:47.60,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's a long stretch that they would have returned to Seattle
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.60,0:59:49.89,辉中,,0,0,0,,and that they would still be there and that they would be findable.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.89,0:59:54.73,辉中,,0,0,0,,But when you're motivated this strongly, you're willing to go and try anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.73,0:59:59.93,辉中,,0,0,0,,In the same way that Abby was so desperate to go and get revenge against Joel.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.93,1:00:04.26,辉中,,0,0,0,,Ellie now is motivated to go to her turf and get revenge against her.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.26,1:00:08.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,Now Tommy wants to go to Seattle by himself, and Hunt Abby down and get revenge.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.82,1:00:11.31,辉中,,0,0,0,,Maria, of course, is not going to let him do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.31,1:00:15.54,辉中,,0,0,0,,But Tommy's main objective is to prevent Ellie from going,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.54,1:00:19.23,辉中,,0,0,0,,he promised Joel that he would take care of Ellie, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.23,1:00:22.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,And in this case, he knows that if Ellie goes to Seattle,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.29,1:00:24.51,辉中,,0,0,0,,her chances of survival aren't very high.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.51,1:00:27.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,So he'd rather go take on those chances himself
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.90,1:00:31.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,and spare Ellie while trying to get revenge for the sake of the both of them,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.77,1:00:33.69,辉中,,0,0,0,,Ellie demands that they either go together,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.69,1:00:36.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,or that Tommy allow Ellie to go with Dina
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.56,1:00:41.13,辉中,,0,0,0,,and some other people with some troops from the camp to get revenge herself.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.13,1:00:46.36,辉中,,0,0,0,,Tommy, of course, rejects this idea and asks for and more time just a day or so
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.36,1:00:48.50,辉中,,0,0,0,,so that he can try and work something out.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.50,1:00:50.55,辉中,,0,0,0,,In this case, he's just buying time.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.55,1:00:52.71,辉中,,0,0,0,,He's made up his mind as to what he's going to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.71,1:00:54.75,辉中,,0,0,0,,We then see Ellie in Joel's grave site.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.75,1:00:56.22,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's a really touching moment,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.22,1:00:59.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,and it reaffirms that Joel is actually gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.82,1:01:01.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,I don't know about you guys.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.35,1:01:06.02,辉中,,0,0,0,,But I had this sort of surreal feeling when I played through this game the first time.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.02,1:01:09.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,I kept saying to myself: Joel can't actually be dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.16,1:01:14.23,辉中,,0,0,0,,For one because we saw that trailer, where Joel was featured later on in the game in Seattle.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.23,1:01:16.74,辉中,,0,0,0,,And for two because Joel is Joel,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.74,1:01:21.42,辉中,,0,0,0,,you can't just kill off Joel that suddenly, there has to be more to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.42,1:01:23.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,But there isn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.52,1:01:26.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,He's dead. This is his grave and it's sad.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.04,1:01:28.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,Ellie then visits Joles house with Dina,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.04,1:01:32.48,辉中,,0,0,0,,picks up his watch from the first game, it's still broken.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.48,1:01:36.30,辉中,,0,0,0,,And also takes his revolver, which you'll be using throughout the rest of the game.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.30,1:01:39.63,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's actually pretty cool that this is where she gets it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.63,1:01:43.17,辉中,,0,0,0,,We do this though, only after exploring his house a little bit,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.17,1:01:46.95,辉中,,0,0,0,,and there's a lot of incredible detail here,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.95,1:01:49.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,and it really encapsulates Joel's character.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.77,1:01:54.66,辉中,,0,0,0,,He's very music heavy and organized his neat and tidy,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.66,1:01:58.02,辉中,,0,0,0,,and his house is also painfully empty.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.02,1:01:59.97,辉中,,0,0,0,,There's a lot of big, empty rooms.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.97,1:02:01.74,辉中,,0,0,0,,And maybe I'm just reading too much into it,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.74,1:02:04.55,辉中,,0,0,0,,but I couldn't help but feel as though there was a lot of space
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.55,1:02:07.17,辉中,,0,0,0,,where Ellie could have stayed if she had wanted to.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.17,1:02:13.76,辉中,,0,0,0,,Like I said earlier, there was no reason other than the emotional turmoil between the two
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.76,1:02:17.01,辉中,,0,0,0,,for Ellie to go and live in the grandmother, sweet out back.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.01,1:02:23.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,But truly everything from the paintings on the walls which we'll come back to later, I promise to,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.52,1:02:30.27,辉中,,0,0,0,,Joel's bed still being a little rough and that there is a space magazine and books by his bed,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.27,1:02:32.38,辉中,,0,0,0,,that he was reading because he's interested in space
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.38,1:02:35.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,like it's … it's so cute, and it's so touching,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.70,1:02:41.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,and it's so painfully sad to know that he's never going to walk through that house ever again.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.10,1:02:42.66,辉中,,0,0,0,,After you grab these items,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.66,1:02:47.61,辉中,,0,0,0,,you walked downstairs and realized that Maria is there sitting with Dina.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.61,1:02:51.19,辉中,,0,0,0,,She informs you that Tommy left on his own already
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.19,1:02:55.83,辉中,,0,0,0,,and is asking that Ellie be locked up to prevent her from following him.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.83,1:02:59.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,Maria is understandably frustrated, angry, Pissed,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.34,1:03:01.89,辉中,,0,0,0,,whatever words you want to associate with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.89,1:03:04.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,But more than anything, she's worried.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.41,1:03:09.93,辉中,,0,0,0,,and she knows that if she sends Ellie and Dina off to try and help Tommy
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.93,1:03:11.91,辉中,,0,0,0,,at least still stand a better chance.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.91,1:03:17.09,辉中,,0,0,0,,So Maria allows Ellie Indiana to leave Jackson with their horses and some extra supplies
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.09,1:03:22.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,so long as they promised to bring back Tommy, when they return, in one piece.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.56,1:03:26.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,This sets up the dual purpose of your journey and theirs.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.12,1:03:30.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,You're going there to kill Abby, but also to save Tommy,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.33,1:03:33.39,辉中,,0,0,0,,although Tommy probably doesn't need much saving.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.39,1:03:36.36,辉中,,0,0,0,,And you'll realize that once we get to Seattle,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.36,1:03:42.87,辉中,,0,0,0,,There's going to be a third purpose in their journey and motivation to everything that they're doing,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.87,1:03:44.31,辉中,,0,0,0,,that's added on top of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.31,1:03:47.24,辉中,,0,0,0,,I find it really interesting that they set up these multiple goals
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.24,1:03:51.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,because it seems as though it just complicates things which I actually like.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.56,1:03:57.57,辉中,,0,0,0,,Having a single quest, we are just going to try and kill one person, is a little bland.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.57,1:03:59.01,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's a little uninteresting.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.01,1:04:04.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,So to see that we have multiple things we're trying to do all at once is a little refreshing.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.26,1:04:10.98,辉中,,0,0,0,,至此 我们来到了游戏的核心内容——西雅图 第一天\NAfter this we jumped to the start of the core game itself, Seattle day 1.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.98,1:04:15.93,辉中,,0,0,0,,序章结束了 该开始游玩游戏的最核心部分了\NAnd after this, we're done with the prologue and ready to move into the core of the game.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.93,1:04:20.31,辉中,,0,0,0,,但在这之前 我想先和大家聊聊此时我的感受\NBut before we do that, I want to discuss our feelings at this point.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.31,1:04:23.43,辉中,,0,0,0,,我一周目玩到这里 我感觉我是充满继续游玩的动力的\NAt this moment in my first run, I felt motivated.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.43,1:04:30.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,同时内心又觉得充满担忧\NYet still pretty dreadful, in again, the pure sense of the word dread overwhelmed me.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.45,1:04:34.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为这类复仇对任何人来说都不会有好下场\NThese revenge quests never end well for anybody,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.62,1:04:38.69,辉中,,0,0,0,,我不禁去想艾莉最后搞砸了 弄得自己死无葬身之地怎么办\Nand I couldn't help but feel as though Ellie was going to totally screw herself over
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.69,1:04:42.93,辉中,,0,0,0,,我不禁去想艾莉最后搞砸了 弄得自己死无葬身之地怎么办\Nand end up dead in a ditch somewhere if she tried to do this.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.93,1:04:45.99,辉中,,0,0,0,,但我觉得这也正是关键所在\NBut again, I think that's kind of the point.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.99,1:04:51.51,辉中,,0,0,0,,玩家需要去融入艾莉 切身体会她的彷徨与疑虑\NThe player should be just as hesitant and doubtful as Ellie is in this pursuit.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.51,1:04:57.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,诚然 艾莉嘴上说着要去怎样怎样砍死埃比还不带眨眼的\NSure, Ellie talks a big game and explains how she's going to go and kill Abby without any remorse,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.12,1:04:59.64,辉中,,0,0,0,,要让埃比为自己的行为付出代价云云\Nand she's going to get revenge for this terrible act.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.64,1:05:03.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,但艾莉自己还是时不时表现出些许的保留态度\NBut she still shows some slight reservations every once in a while.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.06,1:05:06.51,辉中,,0,0,0,,她深知自己的行为在逻辑上是不合理的\NShe knows that this doesn't make a lot of logical sense
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.51,1:05:11.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,就像埃比最初肯定也知道自己一头扎进暴雪中的杰克逊小镇\Nin the same way that Abby knew that her plan to just go in storm Jackson
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.05,1:05:13.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,也没什么逻辑可言\Ndidn't make a lot of logical sense,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.35,1:05:18.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,但她们都去做了 因为她们认为这似乎是正确的\Nbut they are going to try and do it because they felt as though it was the right thing to do,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.21,1:05:20.19,辉中,,0,0,0,,这也是她们坚持下去的原因\Nand that's what kept them going.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.19,1:05:23.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,这是一场情感与动机的拉锯战\NIt's a tug of war of emotions and motivations.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.40,1:05:26.88,辉中,,0,0,0,,这样的冲突才会造就有趣的故事\NAnd that conflict is what makes an interesting story.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.88,1:05:30.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,你可以说你对TLOU2这部分故事有自己的见解\NSay what you will about TLOU2 at this point in the story.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.96,1:05:33.15,辉中,,0,0,0,,但游戏本身还是有趣的\NBut it's interesting and engaging,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.15,1:05:37.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,可能剧情不是那种令人开心的爽剧\Nnone the less, might not be fun might not be enjoyable,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.41,1:05:39.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,但对我来讲游戏还是很有意思的\Nbut it's interesting at least to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.45,1:05:43.50,辉中,,0,0,0,,可能会有人不喜欢 那我也欢迎大家在下面留言\NMaybe you hated it, and if you did, I would love to hear your thoughts down below,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.50,1:05:47.37,辉中,,0,0,0,,不过说真的 可能不喜欢的人早就关掉视频了\Nbut to be perfectly honest, you're probably not still here in this video.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.37,1:05:50.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,如果这游戏没有任何一点让你觉得有趣的地方\NIf you don't find the story of this game, at least somewhat interesting,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.82,1:05:56.49,辉中,,0,0,0,,还看了一个多小时序章的测评内容 你要还没关视频那大哥你真是纯爷们\NI mean, after all, we just got through the prologue and we are well over an hour into this video.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.49,1:06:02.55,辉中,,0,0,0,,So it's with that newfound motivation to find Abby that we enter the core of the game.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.55,1:06:05.66,辉中,,0,0,0,,And it's good that we have this emotional drive behind us
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.66,1:06:09.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,because we're about to enter a very slow sequence of the game.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.77,1:06:16.98,辉中,,0,0,0,,Seriously there's moments in here where I became actively bored because it was all puzzle solving in platform.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.98,1:06:19.14,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's just kind of blaaaah
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.14,1:06:20.67,辉中,,0,0,0,,but don't worry, we're going to get into it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.67,1:06:24.46,辉中,,0,0,0,,And with that we move to Seattle Day 1.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.46,1:06:28.24,辉中,,0,0,0,,Our first day in Seattle starts with the gate,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.24,1:06:31.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,basically riding through the forest, talking with Dina.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.05,1:06:33.75,辉中,,0,0,0,,And you have to try and get into the body of the city.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.75,1:06:36.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,Of course, there's a lot of military installations that were put up
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.81,1:06:41.97,辉中,,0,0,0,,towards the end of quarantine that have since fallen to pieces.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.97,1:06:43.89,辉中,,0,0,0,,But nonetheless you have to get through them.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.89,1:06:46.17,辉中,,0,0,0,,There's a few supplies here and there that you can gather.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.17,1:06:49.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,But for the most part, this is a puzzle solving sequence.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.12,1:06:54.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,We climbed some buildings go up some ladders enter some codes that we find on some papers
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.34,1:06:56.49,辉中,,0,0,0,,and we push into Seattle.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.49,1:06:59.22,辉中,,0,0,0,,This was probably my least favorite part of the game.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.22,1:07:00.67,辉中,,0,0,0,,We're emotionally motivated.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.67,1:07:03.13,辉中,,0,0,0,,We want to go, kick some ass and take some names
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.13,1:07:06.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,and then give those names to other people whose asses we've kicked,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.21,1:07:11.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,but instead we're forced to just slowly solved some basic puzzles.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.07,1:07:14.13,辉中,,0,0,0,,Write down some codes, walked to another place,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.13,1:07:19.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,pull open our note book to look back at what the codes were and then enter those in manually.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.29,1:07:20.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's not that interesting,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.70,1:07:25.59,辉中,,0,0,0,,and it is in direct conflict with what the player wants to be doing at this point.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.59,1:07:28.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,I understand may be Naughty Dog wanted to slow the pace down
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.62,1:07:33.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,after how emotionally distraught you might be after the prologue.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.18,1:07:37.14,辉中,,0,0,0,,But still, I can't help but feel as though there would have been a better way to do this
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.14,1:07:41.61,辉中,,0,0,0,,may be some more combat sequences, may be introducing you to a new type of infected.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.61,1:07:45.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure, anything I think would have been better than this.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.34,1:07:51.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,We get to downtown and by my estimation, this is the largest single area of the game.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.00,1:07:54.30,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's very open, and there's about eleven main locations,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.30,1:07:58.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,at least that I found to explore in this little area.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.68,1:08:03.57,辉中,,0,0,0,,This includes a bank, a synagogue, a court house all very well realized.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.57,1:08:08.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,The bank is cool because it's frozen in time, right after a group of people tried to rob,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.16,1:08:11.79,辉中,,0,0,0,,I loved seeing all of the money strewn throughout the bank
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.79,1:08:15.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,and watching Allie and Dina ponder what they would do with that money
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.68,1:08:19.38,辉中,,0,0,0,,if it actually was worth anything in their world.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.38,1:08:23.22,辉中,,0,0,0,,And I gotta say Naughty Dog is really good at this sort of indirect world building,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.22,1:08:27.69,辉中,,0,0,0,,it makes you question your actual priorities in your current life.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.69,1:08:30.64,辉中,,0,0,0,,If you're motivated purely by money and you have fat stack
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.64,1:08:33.39,辉中,,0,0,0,,sitting next to you as you watch this video,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.39,1:08:36.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,you can't help but feel a little bit strange
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.45,1:08:41.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,when you walk into this post apocalyptic world and the money is absolutely useless.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.34,1:08:45.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's those types of little things that get the wheels turning in your mind
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.41,1:08:49.17,辉中,,0,0,0,,to start putting yourself in the shoes of the characters in that world.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.17,1:08:55.50,辉中,,0,0,0,,That makes Naughty Dog so good at motivating players to continue engaging with the story.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.50,1:08:57.75,辉中,,0,0,0,,My favorite part of this chapter, however,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.75,1:09:01.92,辉中,,0,0,0,,is an optional item interaction in the music store of this section.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.92,1:09:07.71,辉中,,0,0,0,,and basically if you interact with the guitar here, Ellie will start playing and singing Take On Me to Dina.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.71,1:09:13.36,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's really beautiful and is another calm moment in this already relaxing section.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.36,1:09:19.11,辉中,,0,0,0,,And I really enjoyed it, and I recommend that you also enjoy it because it's not going to last.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.11,1:09:23.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,But while the story elements of this section of the game are pretty impressive,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.82,1:09:29.38,辉中,,0,0,0,,我觉得你要探索的广阔区域并不像我认为顽皮狗希望的那样令人印象深刻\NI don't feel as though the expansive areas that you're meant to explore are quite as impressive
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.38,1:09:32.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,我觉得你要探索的广阔区域并不像我认为顽皮狗希望的那样令人印象深刻\Nas I think Naughty Dog was hoping they would be.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.25,1:09:35.76,辉中,,0,0,0,,This whole area is very reminiscent of the opening of The Lost Legacy,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.76,1:09:39.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,Naughty Dog's, other most recent Uncharted game.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.12,1:09:42.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,In The Lost Legacy, You have a huge open expanse to explore.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.81,1:09:44.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,But by explore,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.07,1:09:48.60,辉中,,0,0,0,,they pretty much mean that you move from one location to the other, fights some bad guys,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.60,1:09:51.75,辉中,,0,0,0,,solve a quick little puzzle and then move to the next area.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.75,1:09:56.61,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's not actually exploring in the same way that you would probably show it in,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.61,1:10:01.23,辉中,,0,0,0,,for instance, The Legend of Zelda: Breath of the Wild, where you're actively exploring the map.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.23,1:10:03.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,Maybe my expectations were just out of check
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.52,1:10:06.60,辉中,,0,0,0,,because Naughty Dog did talk these sections up a lot,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.60,1:10:11.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,saying that these were the largest levels they had ever designed in any of their games ever,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.52,1:10:15.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,which is true in their pretty impressive on that front.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.81,1:10:22.26,辉中,,0,0,0,,But in the age of Red Dead Redemption 2 riding a horse through a field really isn't an incredible achievement.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.26,1:10:25.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,Now, of course, it's not a competition between Naughty Dog and Rockstar.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.77,1:10:30.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,They're both the prettiest girl in the ball, and you can't have either of them,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.00,1:10:35.37,辉中,,0,0,0,,but I can't help but notice as though the foliage and the horses in Red Dead Redemption 2
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.37,1:10:42.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,looked a lot better two years ago, in an open world game, when compared to those in TLOU2.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.35,1:10:47.31,辉中,,0,0,0,,Maybe I'm just really picky or may be my preferences are a skew.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.31,1:10:48.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,Let me know in the comments section below.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.90,1:10:54.54,辉中,,0,0,0,,But I really do feel as though there's a strong difference between these two and it's in Red Dead's favor.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.54,1:10:58.98,辉中,,0,0,0,,Nonetheless, you continue exploring the map and eventually pushed through the gate that was locked,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.98,1:11:00.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,keeping you in this area,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.72,1:11:04.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,everything's quiet and you simply ride your horse through the checkpoint,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.77,1:11:07.47,辉中,,0,0,0,,at least until this happens.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.61,1:11:48.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,We open back up with Ellie, tied to a desk in a small elementary school called Eastbrook.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.96,1:11:52.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,This is not really important, what's important is that l is being held hostage,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.80,1:11:55.02,辉中,,0,0,0,,and Dina seems to have escaped.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.02,1:12:01.11,辉中,,0,0,0,,Ellie is about to be executed when Dina comes in and saves the day … Well, at least … almost.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.09,1:12:07.59,辉中,,0,0,0,,You watches this guy tries to strangle Dina, feeling absolutely helpless.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.59,1:12:09.48,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's actually pretty well done.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.48,1:12:12.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,I found my heart rate increasing quite drastically during this.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.96,1:12:15.39,辉中,,0,0,0,,Eventually, use your foot to grab a shard of glass,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.39,1:12:16.86,辉中,,0,0,0,,use it to cut your bindings.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.86,1:12:20.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,And Ellie goes up and kills Dina's attacker,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.10,1:12:23.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,at which point she grabs a letter and picture from his pocket.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.52,1:12:26.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,Which will be important in just a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.04,1:12:29.97,辉中,,0,0,0,,You are through a few combat sequences here that pair you against human enemies.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.97,1:12:35.49,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's a nice change of pace from the infected that you've been dealing with exclusively up to this point,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.49,1:12:37.92,辉中,,0,0,0,,and it forces you to change your approach.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.92,1:12:41.46,辉中,,0,0,0,,For instance, you have to really be careful managing your flashlights.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.46,1:12:45.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,Going up against most infected, you don't have to worry about your flashlight being on or off
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.32,1:12:48.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,because they can't see it or don't respond to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.70,1:12:51.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,With humans, of course they do.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.21,1:12:54.03,辉中,,0,0,0,,They're much more visual and much less auditory,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.03,1:12:58.71,辉中,,0,0,0,,though tactically flank you and maneuver around you if they need to,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.71,1:13:03.15,辉中,,0,0,0,,though they can be lured with sound into traps very easily.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.15,1:13:07.59,辉中,,0,0,0,,But on survivor difficulty, I will say it can be frustrating if you run out of ammo,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.59,1:13:13.31,辉中,,0,0,0,,as your only option in dealing with them and ranged attacks is to throw bottles and rush
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.31,1:13:15.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,or just sit and pray that they come around.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.78,1:13:21.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,I understand that it's a post apocalyptic world, and not everything is going to be convenient within it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.21,1:13:24.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,But nonetheless, it's pretty frustrating.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.12,1:13:25.74,辉中,,0,0,0,,After fighting your way to safety,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.74,1:13:30.57,辉中,,0,0,0,,Ellie looks at the document and the picture that she swiped off of Dina's attacker.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.57,1:13:36.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's a new picture that Leah gave to her boyfriend, Jordan, who is actually the guy that you just killed.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.32,1:13:40.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,但抱歉了各位 照片上有块血污挡住了关键信息\NAnd sorry boys, but there's a blood smear that covers all of the good stuff,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.32,1:13:42.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以暂停视频肯定没用啦\Nso no use in pausing the video.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.84,1:13:47.46,辉中,,0,0,0,,Now, Leah happens to be one of the people that joined Abby on their "kill-cation",
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.46,1:13:52.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,another coincidence that leads Ellie to the Channel 13 Station to find Leah,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.44,1:13:55.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,who might be able to help them find the Abby in turn.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.77,1:14:03.15,辉中,,0,0,0,,Ellie and Dina also hear about this guy Isaac in conversations that can be overheard from the WLF members.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.15,1:14:10.14,辉中,,0,0,0,,Now not much is known about this guy or revealed about him for that matter, for quite a while.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.14,1:14:15.66,辉中,,0,0,0,,But what we do know is that he seemingly runs the WLF, and he has a firm grip on power.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.66,1:14:18.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,Everyone does what he says and are scared of him.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.21,1:14:23.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,Naughty Dog games of the past would use this as a set up for the later boss fight with Isaac.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:23.16,1:14:26.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,既然提到他了 那他在游戏后面肯定是个关键角色了对吧？\NIf he's mentioned, he'll be a key part of the story later, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.82,1:14:28.65,辉中,,0,0,0,,恭喜你答错了\NWell, actually wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.65,1:14:33.24,辉中,,0,0,0,,这样的事情还会在未来另一个角色身上发生 可能是为续作之类的内容做准备\NThis will happen again with another character later, maybe it's a set up for a sequel or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.24,1:14:40.26,辉中,,0,0,0,,但就伊萨克和另一位即将登场女性角色来说 这样的事情的确没有发生\NBut … as for Isaac himself and the other lady that's going to be shown off, it actually doesn't come around.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.26,1:14:45.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,总之接下来艾莉和蒂娜继续前往城市中心 寻找13频道电视台\NAll of that said Ellie and Dina head into the heart of the city to find the Channel 13 Station
Dialogue: 0,1:14:45.00,1:14:49.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,追捕利娅 想办法从她那里获得更多埃比的消息\Nto hunt down Leah to try and in turn, get more information on Abby.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.08,1:14:53.67,辉中,,0,0,0,,你继续推进 顺手杀了一堆WLF士兵和感染者\NYou push through a ton of WLF soldiers and lots of infected as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.67,1:14:58.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,你发现地上有绊雷 不禁想起一代里的比尔\NYou find some trip wire traps set up that reminded me of Bill from the first game.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.29,1:15:03.99,辉中,,0,0,0,,但在这里它们除了减慢游戏探索速度之外似乎没有任何作用\NBut here they don't seem to serve any purpose other than to slow down game play and exploration then.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.99,1:15:09.30,辉中,,0,0,0,,就我个人而言我很快发现这些绊雷的乐趣所在——它们就是单纯的烦\NPersonally I just soon find these trip wire bombs fun. They're just annoying.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.30,1:15:13.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,偶尔用一些新的不同的东西来为单调的游戏调味的想法是好的\NIt's good to shake up the monotony of game play every once in a while that something new and different,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.68,1:15:15.63,辉中,,0,0,0,,比如这些绊雷\Nsuch as these trip wire minds.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.63,1:15:20.19,辉中,,0,0,0,,而在这里 这些绊雷并没有在游戏剩余部分中出现\NBut in this case, these things don't really come up again for the rest of the game.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.19,1:15:26.76,辉中,,0,0,0,,它们只是一种不会让你形成游戏中新的习惯行为的烦人道具\NThey're just a one of frustration that doesn't actually drive you into any sort of new habitual behavior.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.76,1:15:30.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,换句话说 在大多数游戏中 制作者向你介绍一个新的游戏元素\NIn other words in most games, when they introduce you to a new gameplay element,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.90,1:15:33.75,辉中,,0,0,0,,其原因是这个元素会在游戏中剩余部分用到\Nit's because it's going to be used throughout the rest of the game,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.75,1:15:36.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以你需要学会掌握它\Nwhich is why you need to be taught how to deal with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.72,1:15:42.24,辉中,,0,0,0,,但在这里 这个元素用的很少 而且很多可以避开\NBut in this case they're used very sparingly and in most cases they are entirely avoidable.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.24,1:15:45.27,辉中,,0,0,0,,当然了 这可能是我自己的小癖好罢了\NBut granted. This is probably just a pet peeve on my end.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.27,1:15:49.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,接下来你会遇到游戏中最棒的收集品\NSo you come up on the station after finding the best collectable in the game.
